In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 2013 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. He acknowledges the significant contribution of African Americans to shaping the American sound, from gospel and Motown to bebop and blues. Obama highlights how African-American musicians have used their music to make change and advance justice throughout history. He calls upon public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and foster appreciation of music composed, arranged, or performed by African Americans.